Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine red-brown. Very hard fired.. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 59, 16. Name Chrysostratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0918.58 and a piece from Kaunos, B.Schmaltz, Die Hellenistischen Amphorenstempel vom Kaunos (Asia Minor Studien 79) 66, KA 149.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0528)
